Write a method that takes an integer n and returns the index of the first '1' bit (starting from index 0 on the right).
Example:If n = 4 (Binary: 100), 
the first '1' is at index 2.
If n = 10 (Binary: 1010), 
the first '1' is at index 1.
If n = 7 (Binary: 0111), 
the first '1' is at index 0.

import java.util.*;
public class main {
    public static void main(String[]args){
    Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
    int n=sc.nextInt();
    int index=0;
    int num;
    while(n>0){
        num=n&1;
        if(num==1){
                System.out.println(index);     
                break;   
        }
        index++;
        n>>=1;
    }
}
}
